{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5e1cf16-9e48-425d-9117-a6fc2b276f1f","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — a file can only reference types/modules from files listed **before** it. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ZQUNSFyemHVCmNIA4xplMm","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9e6707e45d124b50ac75e6d6aa908993/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9e6707e45d124b50ac75e6d6aa908993/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4dcfb21d-e20e-476e-83ae-36a1a229115f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj` file:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs` in the compilation order.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"5BD3:2056C4:4845F28:4FE8DAC:69F9E5DE"},"id":"cc782815-61d7-44a5-a07b-d27e48d51080","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:43:18.760Z","parentId":"bdf64ff3-4e4f-4148-a60d-8a03b813626f"}
